<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Remarks from a &quot;youg&quot; tester (Beta 4 only): Pets &amp; PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?LoneCat">LoneCat</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:53 p.m. 11/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Remarks from a &quot;youg&quot; tester (Beta 4 only): Pets &amp; PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Most of my message will deal with PETS, if it was already discussed pleased put a link in an answer. Thanks =)

<P>1) While a master (lvl 12) cannot attack an opponent (lvl 5 for exemple), he can summon a pet which will then be able to do the job. He will also be able to heal it, to summon other pets if necessary, etc ...
<P>I think the lvl of the master should be taken into account and not the lvl of the pet.
<P>2) The pets were able to attack people in town, without any reaction from the guard, neither against the pet, nor against the master.
<P>I think the guards should attack the pet and then the master (as if he would attack himself the victim)
<P>1 and 2 together make it impossible to flee from a high lvl Necro or Magician PKer, even inside a city =(
<P>3) About one week ago, a friend and I created 2 newbies to make a test: I killed him 10 times and each time I checked the attitude of the nearest guard (we were both humans). The attitude was always the same (indifferently ...). Apparently the faction standing was not modified by the kills ?!?!?!
<P>Is the faction standing now operating ?
<P>Thanks, and again please excuse me if these points have already been discussed.
<BR>Ciao,
<BR>LoneCat
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
